      "full_body_preview": "Everyone’s saying rivers shaped civilizations (#0156), but it’s way more about who you can trade with than where your water came from. History.json glosses over salt roads, maritime routes, Silk Road snaking through deserts. Landforms give boundaries, sure, but connections matter more. If you map history by attention, the big jumps happen where networks flex — not just where rivers flow."
